    section#main
      .title.is-family-secondary.is-4 About me
      p I'm a self-taught Pythonista with a background in audio and electronics engineering. I write code for a living, with a focus on data acquisition and UI/UX. In my off time, I play the guitar, fix things, and make new things. My current passion project is my custom-designed mechanical keyboard called <abbr title="Dual Ergolinear Low-Profile Human Interface">DELPHI</abbr>. You can learn more about it and some of my other projects below.
      br
      p My tecnical areas of interest include (in no particular order) mechanical keyboards, guitar tech, PCB design, MSLA (resin) 3D printing, web dev, game dev, graphic design, and more...
      br
      p My <i>non-technical</i> areas of interest include Dungeons &amp; Dragons, astronomy and astropyhsics, craft beer, pixel art, linguistics, video games, cooking, and science fiction just to name a few!

    section#projects
      .title.is-family-secondary.is-4 Projects
      p Almost every project starts as an excuse to learn something new or practice something I've learned. Here's what I've been working on lately:
      br
      .columns
        .column
          .panel.is-light
            .panel-heading.is-family-secondary DELPHI
            .panel-block
              a(href="https://github.com/JRiggles/DELPHI-kbd" target="_blank")
                img(
                  src="https://github.com/JRiggles/DELPHI-kbd/blob/main/images/DELPHI%20photo.png?raw=true"
                  alt="a photo of my custom keyboard called DELPHI"
                )
            .panel-block
              p.is-family-primary A.K.A. "Dual Ergolinear Low-Profile Human Interface". DELPHI is a minimal split mechanical keyboard designed to combine ergonomics and an ortholinear layout into a small form factor.
            .panel-footer
              .panel-block
